  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part">A <b>Part</b> is a type of <b>Product</b> that is intended to be produced or employed in a production process.
   A <b>Part</b> may represent either a single piece part, an assembly of parts, or a raw material.
	 
  <note>A complex instance of the <b>Part</b> entity and of the <express_ref linkend="Document_and_version_identification:arm:Document_and_version_identification_arm.Document">Document</express_ref> entity may be created in order to represent a document that is a component of a manufactured product, for example a user manual of a car.
	</note>
	</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part  Where: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part.wr:WR1">The part shall belong to a product category named 'part' or to a product category named 'raw material'.
   </ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part_version
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version">A <b>Part_version</b> is a type of <b>Product_version</b> that identifies a version of a part.
<note>A <b>Part_version</b> is expected to be functionally and physically interchangeable with the other versions of the same <b>Part</b>.</note>
   </ext_description>

  <!--
